The paper deals with vulnerability detection in software, which is a common topic in the computer security (cs.CR) sub-category. The paper also presents a novel fuzzing framework, which involves symbolic execution and program analysis, making it relevant to the software engineering (cs.SE) and programming languages (cs.PL) sub-categories. The use of symbolic execution also makes it relevant to the systems and control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses machine learning techniques to improve the effectiveness of the fuzzing framework, which makes it relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
